medical_history.chief_complaint: Severe retrosternal chest pain, nausea, and palpitations.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began 1 or 2 hours after consuming mixed vodka and energy drinks, lasting for 10 hours. Initially presented with nausea and multiple episodes of emesis, evolving into constant chest pain described as pressure. Symptoms were aggravated by the energy drink intake.
medical_history.family_history: No family history of premature coronary artery disease.
medical_history.social_history: Patient smokes no more than 5 cigarettes weekly and used marijuana in the week prior but denied cocaine or other recreational drug use.
